There is a closed screen door leading east. There is a closed frosted-glass door leading north. You don't like doors? Why not try going west, that entranceway is not blocked by one.

There is a closed screen door leading east. There is a closed frosted-glass door leading north. You don't like doors? Why not try going west, that entranceway is not blocked by one.

-= Kitchen =-
You've walked into a standard room. Your mind races to think of what kind of room would be standard. And then it hits you. Of course. You're in the kitchen.

You see a fridge. As if things weren't amazing enough already, you can even see an oven. You look at the price tag that the oven's owner still hasn't taken off. Thirty big ones?! Where'd they buy this oven, some kind of expensive store? You can make out a table. The table is massive. However, the table, like an empty table, has nothing on it. You make out a counter. What a coincidence, weren't you just thinking about a counter? On the counter you see a cookbook. Classic TextWorld. You make out a stove. What a coincidence, weren't you just thinking about a stove? The stove is conventional. Looks like someone's already been here and taken everything off it, though.

There is a closed screen door leading east. There is a closed frosted-glass door leading north. You don't like doors? Why not try going west, that entranceway is not blocked by one.

-= Kitchen =-
You've walked into a standard room. Your mind races to think of what kind of room would be standard. And then it hits you. Of course. You're in the kitchen.

You see a fridge. As if things weren't amazing enough already, you can even see an oven. You look at the price tag that the oven's owner still hasn't taken off. Thirty big ones?! Where'd they buy this oven, some kind of expensive store? You can make out a table. The table is massive. However, the table, like an empty table, has nothing on it. You make out a counter. What a coincidence, weren't you just thinking about a counter? On the counter you see a cookbook. Classic TextWorld. You make out a stove. What a coincidence, weren't you just thinking about a stove? The stove is conventional. Looks like someone's already been here and taken everything off it, though.

There is a closed screen door leading east. There is a closed frosted-glass door leading north. You don't like doors? Why not try going west, that entranceway is not blocked by one.

-= Kitchen =-
You've walked into a standard room. Your mind races to think of what kind of room would be standard. And then it hits you. Of course. You're in the kitchen.

You see a fridge. As if things weren't amazing enough already, you can even see an oven. You look at the price tag that the oven's owner still hasn't taken off. Thirty big ones?! Where'd they buy this oven, some kind of expensive store? You can make out a table. The table is massive. However, the table, like an empty table, has nothing on it. You make out a counter. What a coincidence, weren't you just thinking about a counter? On the counter you see a cookbook. Classic TextWorld. You make out a stove. What a coincidence, weren't you just thinking about a stove? The stove is conventional. Looks like someone's already been here and taken everything off it, though.

There is a closed screen door leading east. There is a closed frosted-glass door leading north. You don't like doors? Why not try going west, that entranceway is not blocked by one.

The stove is conventional. Looks like someone's already been here and taken everything off it, though.

There is a closed screen door leading east. There is a closed frosted-glass door leading north. You don't like doors? Why not try going west, that entranceway is not blocked by one.

feedback_history.text:
-= Kitchen =-
You've walked into a standard room. Your mind races to think of what kind of room would be standard. And then it hits you. Of course. You're in the kitchen.

You see a fridge. As if things weren't amazing enough already, you can even see an oven. You look at the price tag that the oven's owner still hasn't taken off. Thirty big ones?! Where'd they buy this oven, some kind of expensive store? You can make out a table. The table is massive. However, the table, like an empty table, has nothing on it. You make out a counter. What a coincidence, weren't you just thinking about a counter? On the counter you see a cookbook. Classic TextWorld. You make out a stove. What a coincidence, weren't you just thinking about a stove? The stove is conventional. Looks like someone's already been here and taken everything off it, though.

There is a closed screen door leading east. There is a closed frosted-glass door leading north. You don't like doors? Why not try going west, that entranceway is not blocked by one.
